node.text: Congratulations to new Hall of Famer @realchriswebber; happy to see him sharing it with @jalenvseverybody. Two of Michigan’s finest.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 09, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and people playing football.

node.text:
Davante Adams to ESPN’s Rob Demovsky on the chances of getting a contract extension done before the season opener, which has been a point where deals have gotten done in the past:

"No. No chance."

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 09, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people playing sports.

node.text: Bucs’ QB Tom Brady will start his NFL record 300th regular-season game tonight.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 09, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and people playing football.

node.text: Saints’ All-Pro DE @camjordan94 is donating $40,000 to Second Harvest Food Bank to help with Hurricane Ida Relief. He’s also doing $4 Cameo videos for fans to raise awareness that one in four Louisiana children are experiencing hunger.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 09, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people playing football.

node.text: Here it goes.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and grass.

node.text: Chargers’ RB Austin Ekeler officially did not participate in practice today due to a hamstring injury.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 08, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people playing football.

node.text: Vikings gave Brian O’Neill a five-year, $92.5 million extension, per source. O’Neill is now contractually tied to Minnesota for the next six seasons. He was in the final season of a four-year rookie deal. The former 2nd-round pick from Pitt is now the second-highest paid right tackle in football.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and grass.

node.text: Texans’ GM Nick Caserio this morning to Payne & Pendergast on @SportsRadio610 regarding Deshaun Watson’s status for Sunday’s opener vs. Jacksonville: “I wouldn’t expect him to play. … I wouldn’t anticipate him playing this Sunday and we’ll recalibrate as we go.”

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and playing football.

node.text: Now a Raven…..

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 07, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and people playing football.

node.text: Having lost RBs J.K. Dobbins and Justice Hill to season-ending injuries, the Ravens are signing veteran RB Le’Veon Bell to their practice squad, per source. He soon is likely to be added to the 53-man roster when ready.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 07, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people playing football and grass.

node.text: Saints are releasing RB Latavius Murray, per source. They asked for a pay reduction yesterday and he refused. Murray is coming off his best season, averaging 4.5 yards per carry and 7.7 yards per catch.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 07, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and ball.

node.text: Seahawks and OT Duane reached agreement on a reworked contract that maxes out at $12 million for this season, per source. The deal converts per-game bonuses to guaranteed money while getting an injury protection benefit for 2022.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on September 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: Ahead of Thursday night’s opener against the Bucs, Cowboys’ QB Dak Prescott was listed as a full participant in today’s practice. All systems go.
